
Amelia, 29 Apr. 1781. Encloses a Return of Men and Arms sent from this County to join Genl. Green in Feby. last. Brooking having been sick at the time, the return is signed by Col. [James] Jenkins. The enclosed Return, dated 24 Feb. 1781 and signed J Jenkins Colo. 2 B, A[melia] M[ilitia], lists 222 officers and men, 204 guns, 32 bayonets, 21 lbs. of powder, 24 lbs. of lead, 14 cartridge boxes, 3 wagons and teams.
